Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1275
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
criminal law and procedure.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 24-4-22-3, AS ADDED BY P.L.153-2018,
2 SECTION 10, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3. (a) This section applies only to low THC
4 hemp extract containing:
5 (1) delta-8 THC;
6 (2) delta-10 THC;
7 (3) hexahydrocannabinol (HHC);
8 (4) tetrahydrocannabinol acetate ester (THCo);
9 (5) tetrahydrocannabinolic acid (THCA);
10 (6) tetrahydrocannabiphorol (THCp); or
11 (7) tetrahydrocannabivarin (THCv).
12 (a) (b) Except as provided in subsection (b), (f), a person may sell
13 low THC hemp extract to which this section applies at retail only if all
14 of the following apply:
15 (1) The packaging complies with the requirements of
16 IC 24-4-21-4.
17 (2) The person prohibits an individual who is less than
2026 IN 1275—LS 7040/DI 106

2
1 twenty-one (21) years of age from entering the person's retail
2 establishment.
3 (3) The person conspicuously displays, on or near every
4 entrance to the person's retail establishment, a sign in
5 boldface type that states "NOTICE: It is unlawful for a
6 person less than twenty-one (21) years old to enter this
7 establishment.".
8 (c) A person that violates this section commits a Class C
9 infraction.
10 (d) Notwithstanding IC 34-28-5-4(c), a civil judgment for an
11 infraction committed under this section must be imposed as
12 follows:
13 (1) If the person at that specific business location has not been
14 issued a citation or summons for a violation of this section in
15 the previous one (1) year, a civil penalty of up to four hundred
16 dollars ($400).
17 (2) If the person at that specific business location has had one
18 (1) citation or summons issued for a violation of this section
19 in the previous one (1) year, a civil penalty of up to eight
20 hundred dollars ($800).
21 (3) If the person at that specific business location has had two
22 (2) citations or summonses issued for a violation of this section
23 in the previous one (1) year, a civil penalty of up to one
24 thousand four hundred dollars ($1,400).
25 (4) If the person at that specific business location has had
26 three (3) or more citations or summonses issued for a
27 violation of this section in the previous one (1) year, a civil
28 penalty of up to two thousand dollars ($2,000).
29 A person may not be issued a citation or summons for a violation
30 of this section more than once every twenty-four (24) hours for
31 each specific business location.
32 (e) The following defenses are available to a person accused of
33 violating subsection (b)(2):
34 (1) The individual produced a driver's license bearing the
35 individual's photograph showing that the individual was at
36 least twenty-one (21) years of age.
37 (2) The individual produced a photographic identification
38 card issued under IC 9-24-16-1 or a similar card issued under
39 the laws of another state or the federal government showing
40 that the individual was at least twenty-one (21) years of age.
41 (3) The appearance of the individual was such that an
42 ordinary prudent person would believe that the individual
2026 IN 1275—LS 7040/DI 106

3
1 was not less than thirty (30) years of age.
2 (4) The individual transported or delivered goods to the
3 person within the scope of the individual's employment.
4 (f) This section does not prohibit the sale or dispensing of low
5 THC hemp extract to an individual at least twenty-one (21) years
6 of age at a pharmacy or health care facility (as defined by
7 IC 16-18-2-161(a)).
8 (b) Before July 1, 2018, a person may sell low THC hemp extract at
9 retail even if the packaging does not comply with the requirements of
10 IC 24-4-21-4.
11 SECTION 2. IC 24-4-22-4 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE JULY 1,
12 2026]. Sec. 4. This section applies after June 30, 2018. A person who
13 violates section 3 of this chapter commits a Class C infraction.
14 However, the violation is a Class B infraction if the person has one (1)
15 prior unrelated judgment for a violation of section 3 of this chapter, and
16 a Class A infraction if the person has two (2) or more prior unrelated
17 judgments for a violation of section 3 of this chapter. These penalties
18 are in addition to any criminal penalties that may be imposed for
19 unlawful possession or distribution of a controlled substance.
